        "content": "<p>fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13048#pullrequestreview-4092823839\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 584769220,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775861644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13048#discussion_r3067064283\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Instead of an <code>enabled</code> flag, maybe <code>mem::forget(decrement)</code> here? LLVM can probably keep <code>enabled</code> from being materialized at runtime, but the forget pattern seems no worse for ergonomics and guarantees that we won't need a <code>bool</code> flag at runtime.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584769222,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775861644
    },
